K8s Commands

kubectl get pods												-
kubectl get services											-
kubectl describe deploy 										- To display the resources on default namespace.
kubectl get ns 													- To get all the namespaces.
kubectl create ns name_of_the_namespace 						- To create a new namespace.
kubectl delete ns name_of_the_namespace							- To delete a namespace. By doing this your whole infrastructure will be deleted.
kubectl apply -f filename.yaml 									- 
kubectl apply -f filename.yaml -n name_of_the_namespace			-
kubectl get deploy -n name_of_the_namespace						- To check if your deployment is ready.
kubectl get pod -n name_of_the_namespace						-
kubectl describe pod name_of_the_pod -n name_of_the_namespace 	- To get the logs of the pod.
kubectl delete pod name_of_the_pod -n name_of_the_namespace		- To delete the mentioned pod.
kubectl get svc -n name_of_the_namespace						- To get the service info which is running or not.
kubectl get service -n name_of_the_namespace					- To get the service info which is running or not.
kubectl get pv -n name_of_the_namespace							- To get the persistant volume output.
kubectl get pv -n name_of_the_namespace	-o wide					- To get better description of persistant volume output.
kubectl get pvc -n name_of_the_namespace						- To get the persistant volume claim output.
kubectl get pvc -n name_of_the_namespace -o wide				- To get better description of persistant volume claim output.